1
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:03,410
You're here.

2
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,440
Have a seat.

3
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,160
I'm sorry

4
00:01:05,360 --> 00:01:06,680
for keeping you waiting.

5
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:07,440
No.

6
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:08,360
I just got here too.

7
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,420
Let's order first.

8
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:10,600
Let's get this straight.

9
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:11,400
It's my treat.

10
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:12,600
To thank you

11
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:14,600
for taking me to your school museum.

12
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,930
Then I'll order the whole menu.

13
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:19,340
You can order the entire menu if you want.

14
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,080
Waiter, we'd like to order.

15
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:21,680
Coming.

16
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,260
Here is your water.

17
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:25,840
Pizza.

18
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,480
And a tiramisu.

19
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:29,320
Okay.

20
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:30,160
Some popcorn chicken.

21
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:30,600
Okay.

22
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:31,480
That's it.

23
00:01:32,039 --> 00:01:33,570
Okay, please wait a moment.

24
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:37,210
Didn't you say you'd order the whole menu?

25
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,560
I want to save the rest for next time.

26
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,039
See how nice you look when you smile.

27
00:01:43,039 --> 00:01:44,300
You should smile more.

28
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:47,840
When I saw you at the Imperial Kiln Museum last time,

29
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,570
you were sitting there all alone looking so down.

30
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:51,640
What happened?

31
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,100
Is something on your mind?

32
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,320
Are you sure you want to know?

33
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:57,520
It'll be a long story.

34
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,800
So,

35
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,200
you have a friend helping you

36
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,919
set you up with another guy.

37
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,759
But there is a girl

38
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:11,880
who got in your friend's way.

39
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:12,400
Right.

40
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,840
Then your friend

41
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:15,160
went to blame this girl.

42
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:15,640
Right.

43
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:17,400
And you spoke up for this girl.

44
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,520
So,

45
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:21,650
your friend turned around and blamed you.

46
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:25,079
I don't mean to judge your situation.

47
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:26,320
Believe me.

48
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,850
If you ran into the same thing as me,

49
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:30,850
you'd be very troubled too.

50
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,440
Trust me.

51
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:35,280
I would never run into something like this.

52
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:36,560
True.

53
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,040
Sometimes I really envy you.

54
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,560
You seem to be able

55
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,360
to handle everything with ease.

56
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:45,600
Not really.

57
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,620
I have my own troubles too.

58
00:02:48,280 --> 00:02:50,320
And lately, I've been so anxious about it

59
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,760
that I can't sleep.

60
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,480
What's wrong?

61
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:57,020
My job at the Imperial Kiln Museum is temporary.

62
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,840
So I've always wanted to become a full-time employee.

63
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,000
But the previous two times,

64
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,800
I failed at the final interview.

65
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,640
I've qualified for the interview again this time.

66
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:08,570
But when I think about the previous failures,

67
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:09,920
I get really nervous.

68
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,460
I'm so anxious that I can't sleep.

69
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,380
I didn't expect

70
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,170
you to have a side like this.

71
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:16,920
So I want to thank you.

72
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,810
Every time I see you,

73
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:20,480
I feel a lot more relaxed.

74
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,880
This is how to do this move, right?

75
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,680
Like this.

76
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:27,400
Students,

77
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,079
starting from today,

78
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,000
we will begin

79
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:34,520
the study and research of the Kintsugi restoration technique.

80
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,360
The first step of the Kintsugi technique

81
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,320
is to use raw lacquer to consolidate the base.

82
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:39,840
This involves brushing raw lacquer

83
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:42,170
onto the cross-sections of the ceramics,

84
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,730
joining them together,

85
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:46,680
and then placing them in a kiln to dry.

86
00:03:47,079 --> 00:03:48,079
This raw lacquer,

87
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,400
as the name suggests,

88
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:52,360
is a substance formed after collecting the raw sap

89
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,800
from the lacquer tree.

90
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:58,280
After this substance dries,

91
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,680
it is corrosion-resistant

92
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,680
and heat-resistant,

93
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:03,520
with a beautiful color and luster.

94
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,440
When applied to ceramics,

95
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,040
it is not only practical,

96
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,760
but also enhances

97
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:12,560
the color and luster of the object.

98
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,280
Class is over.

99
00:04:57,159 --> 00:04:57,960
Class is over.

100
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,200
Want to eat together?

101
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,360
I have something to do.

102
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,280
I'm leaving now. Bye.

103
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:01,920
Bye.

104
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,700
What are you doing?

105
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,080
In class.

106
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,960
How's your interview prep going?

107
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,840
You're replying to messages in class?

108
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,100
Go focus on your class.

109
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,810
Mind your own business.

110
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,720
Class dismissed.

111
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,040
Xiaocen,

112
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:19,980
have you thought about it?

113
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,800
About what?

114
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:25,090
Helping out at Fang Xiaqing's studio.

115
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:29,900
Is it appropriate?

116
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:31,440
Yes, of course it is.

117
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:34,680
Besides, we can finish our homework there.

118
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,460
Let's have dinner with them tonight.

119
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,400
Dinner?

120
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,020
There you go again.

121
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,840
I just feel like

122
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,880
maybe they

123
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,960
only want you to go.

124
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,680
If I go, I won't be of much help.

125
00:05:58,680 --> 00:05:59,760
Of course not.

126
00:06:03,640 --> 00:06:05,080
But I...

127
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:17,280
Xu Xiao.

128
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,170
I think you're a talent.

129
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:20,500
When you graduate,

130
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,880
you don't even need to look for a job.

131
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,760
Just join Banlan Studio directly.

132
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,480
We cover food, accommodation, and getting rich.

133
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,210
How about it?

134
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,010
Actually, my skills

135
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,409
are still in the learning process.

136
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:33,960
I can give it a try.

137
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:36,850
Xiao Cen,

138
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,720
what do you think?

139
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,159
I...

140
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:41,840
Yeah.

141
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,040
Xiaocen,

142
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,400
we

143
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,880
also really hope you can join us.

144
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,800
But

145
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:52,480
I'm not as good as Xu Xiao.

146
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,659
I'm afraid I won't be of much help.

147
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,720
Who said that?

148
00:06:57,640 --> 00:06:59,370
Your drawing skills are great.

149
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,620
Yeah, Xiaocen.

150
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:01,760
Don't be modest.

151
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,600
Stay and join us

152
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,740
to create better works together,

153
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,200
okay?

154
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,840
Yeah, stay.

155
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:13,680
Alright.

156
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,520
I think that's a yes.

157
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,640
Then come on, let's have a drink.

158
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,520
Come on, cheers.

159
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,040
Let's have a drink.

160
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:18,500
Come on.

161
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:19,760
Come on.

162
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,000
Cheers.

163
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,450
No need to see us out.

164
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,560
From today on,

165
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:30,160
you are employees of Banlan.

166
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:32,000
Then you'll start working tomorrow.

167
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,840
Just come over when you don't have classes.

168
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:34,320
Okay.

169
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,680
Tell me what you want to eat.

170
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,810
I'll make it for you.

171
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:37,440
Okay.

172
00:07:37,440 --> 00:07:38,840
All right, stop talking.

173
00:07:38,840 --> 00:07:39,760
Or it'll be tomorrow.

174
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:40,360
Bye.

175
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,610
Then we are leaving.

176
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:41,960
Bye.

177
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:42,640
Be safe on your way.

178
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,040
Bye.

179
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:43,880
Bye.

180
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,400
Everyone is so friendly.

181
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:49,960
Yeah.

182
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,320
Actually...

183
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:57,080
What's wrong?

184
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,659
Actually, I was thinking,

185
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:02,280
Sister Xia Qing wants your skills.

186
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,360
I might not be able to help.

187
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,450
That's not true.

188
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:08,880
I'm used to working with you.

189
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,180
From Mr. Yue's class to the antique shop,

190
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,920
I've always worked with you,

191
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:14,520
haven't I?

192
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,170
Don't worry.

193
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,210
You can do it.

194
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:19,890
Let's go.

195
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,120
Okay.

196
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,360
Where are we?

197
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,360
My friend's exhibition hall.

198
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:00,600
It happens to be vacant for the next couple of days.

199
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,000
Why did you bring me here?

200
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,000
Aren't you having your interview soon?

201
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,080
I figured these couple of days

202
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:07,080
would be when you're the most nervous.

203
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,520
So I came up with an idea.

204
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:09,360
Look.

205
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,040
This is...

206
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,400
This is the map of the museum.

207
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:20,920
Yes.

208
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:22,440
Did I draw it accurately?

209
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,160
Why did you draw this?

210
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:26,640
Now,

211
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,530
pretend this is the Imperial Kiln Museum.

212
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:31,200
It's filled with countless

213
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,060
extremely beautiful treasures.

214
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:36,040
And I am your first visitor.

215
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,960
Now, you need to use the lines at your feet

216
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:39,160
and your memory

217
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,490
to explain all the collections here to me.

218
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,800
Now.

219
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,440
I have paid for a human guide.

220
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,120
All right.

221
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:51,740
Please.

222
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,160
Welcome to Jingdezhen Imperial Kiln Museum.

223
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:56,560
I am your guide, Qi Yi.

224
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,400
The first thing we see

225
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,930
is our most treasured piece, the Suisui Duck.

226
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,800
From the Chenghua period of the Ming Dynasty,

227
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,880
a plain sancai duck-shaped incense burner.

228
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,680
Due to the extreme difficulty of the craftsmanship

229
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,760
and the strict selection system of the imperial kiln back then,

230
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,440
it was smashed and buried deep in Zhushan for over 500 years.

231
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,800
Unearthed by archaeologists in 1987,

232
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,640
it is unique to the imperial kiln

233
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,240
and has not been handed down.

234
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,000
What we are looking at now

235
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,480
is the blue-and-white vat with cloud and dragon patterns.

236
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,640
Its main function is to store water.

237
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:27,960
Next, we will see

238
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,330
the three-pot communicating vessel.

239
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:32,970
Alright.

240
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:34,880
That's all for today's tour.

241
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,160
I hope you enjoyed it.

242
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:39,920
Look at you.

243
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,960
You don't even need to be in a real museum

244
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:44,960
to know all the collections like the back of your hand.

245
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,800
You explained them so well blindly.

246
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,930
One hundred points.

247
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,040
During the real interview,

248
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:51,400
if only I could be as relaxed as I am with you.

249
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,720
The reason you get nervous

250
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:54,040
is because whenever

251
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,800
the words 'Imperial Kiln Museum' are mentioned,

252
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,660
it brings back your bad memories.

253
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,240
So I came up with a way.

254
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,850
I want to create a new memory for you

255
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,160
to erase those bad ones from before.

256
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,280
A new memory?

257
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,240
Yeah.

258
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,480
I hope you remember today.

259
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,280
In this imaginary museum,

260
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,760
you fluently

261
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:17,680
and smoothly explained all the collections to me.

262
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,040
This way, during your interview,

263
00:11:20,040 --> 00:11:21,100
if you get nervous,

264
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,040
you can think of today,

265
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,720
this very moment,

266
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:26,220
and think of me.

267
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:29,680
So,

268
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:31,280
did today's memory

269
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,570
overwrite the shadows of the past?

270
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:36,800
Thank you.

271
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,120
Its name is Xiaoguai.

272
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,840
It used to be a stray cat around here.

273
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:49,160
But everyone in our studio often fed it,

274
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,770
so it came here a lot.

275
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,410
Then we also bathed it, clipped its nails,

276
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,200
and gave it delicious food.

277
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,680
So it just stayed here and wouldn't leave.

278
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,280
It really likes being pet on the head like this.

279
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,160
Xiaoguai.

280
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,160
Xiaoguai.

281
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,530
You are all here.

282
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,210
Let's go.

283
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,200
Come here. I have something to announce.

284
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:06,730
Let's go.

285
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,840
Let me tell you two something.

286
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,720
Before you two joined Banlan,

287
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:13,720
Xiaqing and I had been working on her solo exhibition.

288
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,400
And while doing this exhibition,

289
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,720
we hope more people

290
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:18,050
can see Xiaqing's works

291
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:20,840
and notice our brand, Banlan.

292
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:22,180
Most importantly,

293
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,420
there is a Boss Qin.

294
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:26,440
If he sees Banlan's potential

295
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,640
and invests heavily,

296
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,800
he can help our brand grow.

297
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:31,440
Um,

298
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:32,560
who is Boss Qin?

299
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,120
A boss Jingjing is currently in contact with.

300
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,160
He is an investor

301
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,200
our studio is trying to win over now.

302
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:41,360
We were originally supposed to start this exhibition

303
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,960
next week.

304
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,080
But Xiaqing told me

305
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,080
she wanted more time

306
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,000
for you guys to help her

307
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,960
polish the final product.

308
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,560
So this exhibition might be postponed.

309
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:54,290
Understood.

310
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,920
Then knock the two ends of the staple we made earlier

311
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:57,780
into the holes.

312
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,810
This way, the broken pieces can be connected.

313
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,400
Let me try.

314
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:03,400
Sure.

315
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,250
Start with this one.

316
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:06,720
Here.

317
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:08,880
Here.

318
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:12,040
Be

319
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:12,480
careful.

320
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:12,880
Okay.

321
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:18,360
The finished product is roughly like this.

322
00:13:18,360 --> 00:13:19,820
Try to cut it a bit smaller.

323
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,560
We still need to knock

324
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,010
and polish it later.

325
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:28,560
You edit very well.

326
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:30,220
I find that I learn quite fast.

327
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,160
You're smart.

328
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,540
You learn it as soon as you are taught.

329
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,960
Xiaoguai is barking.

330
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,930
Did Jingjing forget to feed it?

331
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,480
I'll go.

332
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,440
Thanks, Xiaocen.

333
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,260
No problem.

334
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:53,600
Xiaoguai.

335
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,370
What are you barking at?

336
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:02,880
What's wrong?

337
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,440
Xu Xiao.

338
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,120
Do you like Xiaocen?

339
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,440
W-What?

340
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,520
You're blushing.

341
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:15,660
No, I'm not.

342
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:17,520
Yes, you are.

343
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:20,880
No.

344
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,740
We're just ordinary classmates.

345
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:26,080
You're not just ordinary classmates.

346
00:14:26,520 --> 00:14:28,360
You clearly care a lot.

347
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:30,080
Care?

348
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,480
No, I don't.

349
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:35,280
Xiaocen just got up to leave,

350
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,500
and you were already looking for her.

351
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,420
If that's not caring, what is?

352
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,320
Don't talk nonsense.

353
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,220
And don't say anything crazy to Xiaocen.

354
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:48,520
Xiaoguai is indeed hungry.

355
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,080
Sit.

356
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,290
Let's continue.

357
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,090
Why did she kill him?

358
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:03,320
They were enemies in their past life.

359
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,520
So in this life,

360
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:06,980
this woman wants to seek revenge on this man.

361
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,960
Then why didn't the man hide?

362
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,400
This man has no memory of his past life.

363
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,240
He loves this woman in this life.

364
00:15:15,680 --> 00:15:17,480
When did he fall in love with her?

365
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:18,320
Sis.

366
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:19,920
Can't you just watch the show properly?

367
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,680
You watch the show for a bit, then do chores.

368
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,410
You can't even follow the plot.

369
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:26,000
I wouldn't be able to follow it if I didn't ask you.

370
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:26,640
Tell me quickly.

371
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:28,370
Then don't ask me. Ask Xiaocen.

372
00:15:28,520 --> 00:15:30,000
You're distracting me from the show.

373
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,800
Xiaocen, tell your mom about it.

374
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,000
Xiaocen.

375
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:35,600
What's wrong?

376
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:37,320
You don't look well.

377
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,650
Is something wrong?

378
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:41,480
What's wrong? Are you feeling unwell?

379
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,280
It's nothing.

380
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:43,400
Really?

381
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:48,600
What's going on at your school recently?

382
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,680
You used to come straight home after school,

383
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:52,680
but now you leave early and come back late every day.

384
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,080
She said she was going to Taoxichuan.

385
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,940
What are you doing in Taoxichuan?

386
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,480
There was an...

387
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,840
an older girl from outside the school,

388
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:01,900
who asked me to help her make pottery.

389
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:02,840
No.

390
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:05,080
Schoolwork is heavy enough.

391
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,160
Things outside of school,

392
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,440
just don't get involved.

393
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,040
Okay?

394
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,280
We don't need you to earn tuition money.

395
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,920
I'm not doing it for money.

396
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,570
If not for money, then what for?

397
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,920
I don't know what for either.

398
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:20,400
You don't know why, yet you're just messing around?

399
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,480
Are you doing this on purpose to make me mad?

400
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,240
No, Mom.

401
00:16:25,280 --> 00:16:26,880
Sis, keep your voice down.

402
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,210
Look how you scared her.

403
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,600
We need to keep Xiaocen happy.

404
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:32,480
A broad mind makes a healthy body.

405
00:16:32,480 --> 00:16:34,480
First of all, she needs a broad mind.

406
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:35,360
Yes.

407
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,080
Okay.

408
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:38,170
I was speaking too loudly just now.

409
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,880
I'm telling you, things outside of school,

410
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:42,240
just don't get involved.

411
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,040
Look at this period of time,

412
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,640
it wasn't easy to get your health back on track.

413
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:46,360
The doctor even said you can stop taking Chinese medicine.

414
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,720
Don't mess around and get sick again.

415
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:49,240
Got it?

416
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:49,880
I got it.

417
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:50,840
Alright, it's late.

418
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:51,920
Hurry up and go to sleep.

419
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:52,560
Go ahead.

420
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:54,140
Go to bed early.

421
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,760
With Xu Xiao's help,

422
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,079
Xia Qing made rapid progress

423
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,900
and soon found a new approach to her work.

424
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,609
The two of them worked together

425
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,359
with great chemistry.

426
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:27,319
I even felt that in just a few days,

427
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:28,840
she had gotten closer to Xu Xiao

428
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:30,480
than I ever was.

429
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,120
I am always like this,

430
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,930
doing everything a few steps slower than others.

431
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,240
The world runs

432
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:41,460
just like the TV series my aunt and mom are watching.

433
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,840
The fast pace leaves me breathless.

434
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:48,690
How I wish the time Xu Xiao and I spent together

435
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,440
could be like the bus that took us home,

436
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,400
moving forward slowly, stop by stop.

437
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:58,440
But I feel like I'm still left on the platform,

438
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,810
not knowing if the last bus hasn't arrived yet

439
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,000
or has already left.

440
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,040
Xiaocen.

441
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:16,850
What are you doing here?

442
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,800
I've finished the hand drawings Xiaoyu and Tian Yuan gave me.

443
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,600
Xiaqing.

444
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:23,260
I have nothing to do right now.

445
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,650
Do you need any help?

446
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:25,140
No need.

447
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:27,050
Everything is going smoothly.

448
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:28,730
This is a cake I made.

449
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:31,920
Jingjing and Xu Xiao both said it was delicious.

450
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,120
I hope you like it too.

451
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:34,840
Thank you.

452
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,160
Enjoy it. I'll get going.

453
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,000
This is so delicious.

454
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:55,320
Xiaocen,

455
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:59,040
Did you notice

456
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,960
if there's anything different

457
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,160
between Wang Lin and Li Zhuoting today?

458
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,400
Sorry, Wu Jing.

459
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,060
I didn't catch a word you said.

460
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,680
Wang Lin, Wang Lin.

461
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:11,920
They are not sitting together.

462
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,920
Keep it down.

463
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:13,720
Yes.

464
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:14,980
Let me tell you.

465
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,440
You have no idea.

466
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:17,800
Xiaoyi.

467
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,160
The three of them are in a complicated situation now.

468
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:20,840
Why?

469
00:21:21,120 --> 00:21:24,440
Xiaoyi and Wang Lin used to be together, right?

470
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,280
After they broke up,

471
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:28,560
Xiaoyi started flirting with Li Zhuoting.

472
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:31,080
So now Wang Lin and Li Zhuoting

473
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,880
are not sitting together anymore.

474
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,080
Look at how they are sitting,

475
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:35,600
like they're at the ends of the earth.

476
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,320
They're forming a triangle.

477
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:40,160
Yeah.

478
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,160
It really is a triangle.

479
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:47,980
Look how awkward they are now.

480
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:51,850
Look.

481
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,000
Class monitor, is everyone here?

482
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:58,840
Everyone is here.

483
00:21:58,840 --> 00:21:59,440
Then,

484
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,980
let's start the class.

485
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:08,170
Xiaocen.

486
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:11,360
Are you going to the antique shop today?

487
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:13,560
Xia Qing and the others went to collect porcelain shards this afternoon.

488
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:15,890
You don't need to go to the studio so early.

489
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:18,440
I won't go this afternoon.

490
00:22:19,760 --> 00:22:21,620
Yuexin is treating me to milk tea.

491
00:22:22,520 --> 00:22:22,960
Let's go.

492
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,600
Milk tea.

493
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,360
Xiao Xu.

494
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,650
I have something to share with you.

495
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:38,640
Do you remember my pair of large chicken-heart walnuts?

496
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:39,520
What about them?

497
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,920
A couple of mornings ago,

498
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,370
as soon as I arrived at the shop,

499
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,680
I found one was suddenly missing.

500
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,320
I was so anxious that I searched in the shop,

501
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:48,780
upstairs and downstairs.

502
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,200
It's been with me for about ten years.

503
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,760
I'm attached to it, you know?

504
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:52,680
Most importantly,

505
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,200
it's called Big Chicken Heart.

506
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,320
Missing one, wouldn't that mean missing a heart?

507
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,120
This is not the strangest thing.

508
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,610
The strangest thing is,

509
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,800
in the afternoon,

510
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:02,320
it suddenly appeared on my desk,

511
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:03,400
in the most obvious place.

512
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,060
Right here,

513
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,450
right in the middle.

514
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:08,280
Don't you think it's too weird?

515
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:11,640
How come when I share something with you,

516
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,000
I get no reaction at all?

517
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,300
Didn't I ask you to come with Xiaocen?

518
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:21,720
There's a bunch of cups in the shop waiting for her to write on.

519
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:22,920
You can't just grab her

520
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:24,040
the moment she takes a break.

521
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:25,240
She needs to rest too.

522
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,120
From what you're saying,

523
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,570
something seems wrong.

524
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:32,760
What's up?

525
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:33,970
Nothing.

526
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:36,200
Did you two fight?

527
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:36,800
We didn't.

528
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:38,020
Then what's wrong?

529
00:23:41,360 --> 00:23:42,090
It's just...

530
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:45,080
I feel like lately

531
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:48,000
she's suddenly become a different person.

532
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,320
Did you make her mad?

533
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,560
Mad about what?

534
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,560
Mad about what?

535
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,560
How would I know?

536
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:01,720
Let me tell you, stop overthinking.

537
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,200
When it comes to women,

538
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,330
even if you pay 120 percent attention,

539
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,640
you can't dodge a single landmine you're meant to step on.

540
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:08,720
When I was young,

541
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,520
I suffered a lot because of this.

542
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:11,770
Stop overthinking.

543
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:12,960
Women...

544
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:15,900
I didn't understand when I was young.

545
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,440
I don't understand it now either.

546
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:18,640
And as for the future,

547
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,360
I probably won't either.

548
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:36,800
Xu Xiao.

549
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,170
Reply to him. Hurry.

550
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,240
Xu Xiao.

551
00:24:55,320 --> 00:24:55,850
Xiaocen.

552
00:24:57,840 --> 00:24:59,570
You asked me to come today to...

553
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:03,780
I want to sincerely

554
00:25:04,480 --> 00:25:05,480
apologize to you.

555
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:07,400
Apologize?

556
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:11,770
Have you been

557
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:13,720
unhappy lately?

558
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:17,360
No.

559
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:22,170
I know you haven't been very happy lately.

560
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:23,080
And I know

561
00:25:23,520 --> 00:25:25,850
you're not someone who gets angry easily.

562
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:29,160
When I interact with others,

563
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,200
I can be a bit slow.

564
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,880
Sometimes I upset people.

565
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,200
So,

566
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:36,280
is it my fault

567
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:38,720
that you're unhappy?

568
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:39,850
It's not your fault.

569
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:42,480
It's me.

570
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:45,800
Young man,

571
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,730
buy a balloon for your girlfriend.

572
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:48,400
Sorry.

573
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,640
We are not in that kind of relationship.

574
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:55,130
It doesn't look like it.

575
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:00,570
Then what can I do to make you a little happier?

576
